            <thetext>While it is actually not needed by qooxdoo&#39;s GUI toolkit, why not pimp up the DOM/CSS part of the framework to include some functionality commonly seen in other low-level JS libraries? This was included in the early days of qooxdoo, but has been removed once it wasn&#39;t needed any longer for the mote advanced layout engine.

When looking at other libraries it is important to make sure the licenses allow integration into qooxdoo (e.g. BSD, MIT, etc.). As an orientation, YUI, jQuery and Prototype could be interesting.

Candidates:
* getElementsByClassName(), http://ejohn.org/blog/getelementsbyclassname-speed-comparison/
* hasClass()
* addClass()
* removeClass()
* replaceClass()
* ...</thetext>
